      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of clinically relevant loading configurations; minimum two load levels or configurations tested.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted under a single ASTM F1717 standard test configuration (62 mm inter-pedicle distance, 5 mm/min displacement rate). Although temperature, humidity, and fixation torque were controlled and documented, only a single test condition was evaluated. This limits the achieved level to Gradation 2, below the required Gradation 3. This shortfall is acknowledged and accepted given that ASTM F1717 specifies a standardized configuration and regulatory precedent supports single-condition validation for this device class."
    },
