    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors were assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors met or exceeded the required gradation level. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) is accepted given ASTM F1717 standardization and regulatory precedent. All three QoIs met pre-specified quantitative acceptance bounds across N=11 constructs at two independent laboratories. The overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support a Medium assurance level conclusion that the FEA model adequately predicts ASTM F1717 compression-bending performance for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct.",
